A-fib can be fleeting and
intermittent; symptoms can be
vague, so many patients dont
seek care.
MEANS A DIFFICULT
DIAGNOSIS.
ECG can be misinterpreted, events
can go uncaught or symptoms can
be attributed to other illnesses (e.g.,
panic attack).
A-Fib must be confirmed
with ECG tracing.
If ECG doesnt catch the
episode, an ambulatory
Holter monitor is worn for
2448 hours.
If events are infrequent,
a cardiac event monitor
can be worn over a
prolonged period.
